## Mini-Game Design Anti-Patterns

### WRONG: No Choice

```
"Click OK to receive 100 cultivation points"
Problem: No decision = no engagement
```

### RIGHT: Meaningful Trade-off

```
"Ổn Định: Safe, slow progress"
"Cưỡng Ép: Fast progress, risk injury"
"Bế Quan: Very fast, but locks your actions"
```

### WRONG: No Failure State

```
"Alchemy always succeeds, just different quality"
Problem: No tension, no stakes
```

### RIGHT: Real Stakes

```
"Alchemy can fail: lose ingredients"
"High quality: requires skilled fire control"
"Đan Kiếp: Cực Phẩm risks catastrophic failure"
```

### WRONG: Pure Randomness

```
"Roll 1d100, higher is better"
Problem: No player agency
```

### RIGHT: Skill + Chance

```
"Choose fire control each round"
"Your choices affect stability"
"Some randomness remains (pure chance events)"
```

